README.md
     1‚Üí# Versioning Library for Go
     2‚Üí
     3‚Üí![Build Status](https://github.com/hashicorp/go-version/actions/workflows/go-tests.yml/badge.svg)
     4‚Üí[![Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/badge/github.com/hashicorp/go-version.svg)](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/hashicorp/go-version)
     5‚Üí
     6‚Üígo-version is a library for parsing versions and version constraints,
     7‚Üíand verifying versions against a set of constraints. go-version
     8‚Üícan sort a collection of versions properly, handles prerelease/beta
     9‚Üíversions, can increment versions, etc.
    10‚Üí
    11‚ÜíVersions used with go-version must follow [SemVer](http://semver.org/).
    12‚Üí
    13‚Üí## Installation and Usage
    14‚Üí
    15‚ÜíPackage documentation can be found on
    16‚Üí[Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/hashicorp/go-version).
    17‚Üí
    18‚ÜíInstallation can be done with a normal `go get`:
    19‚Üí
    20‚Üí```
    21‚Üí$ go get github.com/hashicorp/go-version
    22‚Üí```
    23‚Üí
    24‚Üí#### Version Parsing and Comparison
    25‚Üí
    26‚Üí```go
    27‚Üív1, err := version.NewVersion("1.2")
    28‚Üív2, err := version.NewVersion("1.5+metadata")
    29‚Üí
    30‚Üí// Comparison example. There is also GreaterThan, Equal, and just
    31‚Üí// a simple Compare that returns an int allowing easy >=, <=, etc.
    32‚Üíif v1.LessThan(v2) {
    33‚Üí    fmt.Printf("%s is less than %s", v1, v2)
    34‚Üí}
    35‚Üí```
    36‚Üí
    37‚Üí#### Version Constraints
    38‚Üí
    39‚Üí```go
    40‚Üív1, err := version.NewVersion("1.2")
    41‚Üí
    42‚Üí// Constraints example.
    43‚Üíconstraints, err := version.NewConstraint(">= 1.0, < 1.4")
    44‚Üíif constraints.Check(v1) {
    45‚Üí	fmt.Printf("%s satisfies constraints %s", v1, constraints)
    46‚Üí}
    47‚Üí```
    48‚Üí
    49‚Üí#### Version Sorting
    50‚Üí
    51‚Üí```go
    52‚ÜíversionsRaw := []string{"1.1", "0.7.1", "1.4-beta", "1.4", "2"}
    53‚Üíversions := make([]*version.Version, len(versionsRaw))
    54‚Üífor i, raw := range versionsRaw {
    55‚Üí    v, _ := version.NewVersion(raw)
    56‚Üí    versions[i] = v
    57‚Üí}
    58‚Üí
    59‚Üí// After this, the versions are properly sorted
    60‚Üísort.Sort(version.Collection(versions))
    61‚Üí```
    62‚Üí
    63‚Üí## Issues and Contributing
    64‚Üí
    65‚ÜíIf you find an issue with this library, please report an issue. If you'd
    66‚Üílike, we welcome any contributions. Fork this library and submit a pull
    67‚Üírequest.
